                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 85.556,
                                "stop": 86.854,
                                "byte_start": 419109,
                                "byte_stop": 424229,
                                "text": "Thank you, Mr. Justice White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86.854,
                        "stop": 305.553,
                        "byte_start": 424229,
                        "byte_stop": 1299017,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15043,
                            "name": "Potter Stewart",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/potter_stewart",
                            "last_name": "Stewart",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2687,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -353962800,
                                    "date_end": 362984400,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2687"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32752,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56350,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/potter_stewart.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8298,
                            "identifier": "potter_stewart"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 86.854,
                                "stop": 96.042,
                                "byte_start": 424229,
                                "byte_stop": 461009,
                                "text": "I have filed a dissenting opinion in the case of Mitchell against W.T. Grant Company."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.042,
                                "stop": 122.774,
                                "byte_start": 461009,
                                "byte_stop": 567902,
                                "text": "In my view this case is constitutionally indistinguishable from the case of Fuentes against Shevin, decided by this Court only two years ago and reported in Volume 407 of the United States Reports, and the Court today has simply rejected the reasoning of that case and adopted instead the analysis of the dissenting opinion in that case written by my brother Mr. Justice White."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.774,
                                "stop": 135.856,
                                "byte_start": 567902,
                                "byte_stop": 620251,
                                "text": "On the reasoning and authority of the Fuentes opinion, I would reverse the judgment before us because the Louisiana sequestration procedure fails to comport with the requirements of due process of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.856,
                                "stop": 145.107,
                                "byte_start": 620251,
                                "byte_stop": 657241,
                                "text": "These views are spelled out in some detailed in the written opinion, I have filed today, but I would add an additional word."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.107,
                                "stop": 154.98,
                                "byte_start": 657241,
                                "byte_stop": 696738,
                                "text": "It seems to me that unless we respect the constitutional decisions of this Court, we can hardly expect that others will do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.98,
                                "stop": 171.482,
                                "byte_start": 696738,
                                "byte_stop": 762776,
                                "text": "A substantial departure from precedent can only be justified, I have thought, in the light of experience with the application of the rule to be abandoned or in the light of an altered historic environment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.482,
                                "stop": 192.299,
                                "byte_start": 762776,
                                "byte_stop": 846054,
                                "text": "Yet the Court today has unmistakably overruled a considered decision of this Court that is barely two years old without pointing to any change in basic constitutional understandings that might justify this total disregard of stare decisis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.299,
                                "stop": 214.625,
                                "byte_start": 846054,
                                "byte_stop": 935393,
                                "text": "The Fuentes decision was in a direct line of recent cases in this Court that have applied the procedural due process commands of the the Fourteenth Amendment to prohibit governmental action that deprives a person of a statutory or contractual property interest with no advance notice and no opportunity to be heard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.625,
                                "stop": 230.602,
                                "byte_start": 935393,
                                "byte_stop": 999236,
                                "text": "In the short time that has elapsed since the Fuentes case was decided, many state and federal courts have followed it in accessing the constitutional validity of state replevin statutes and other comparable state laws."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.602,
                                "stop": 250.728,
                                "byte_start": 999236,
                                "byte_stop": 1079798,
                                "text": "No data have been brought to our attention to indicate that these decisions, granting to otherwise defenseless consumers, the simple rudiments of due process of law have worked any untoward change in the consumer credit market or in other commercial relationships."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 250.728,
                                "stop": 259.759,
                                "byte_start": 1079798,
                                "byte_stop": 1115847,
                                "text": "The only perceivable change that has occurred since the Fuentes case is in the make up of this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.759,
                                "stop": 277.481,
                                "byte_start": 1115847,
                                "byte_stop": 1186795,
                                "text": "A basic change in the law upon a ground, no firmer than a change in this Court\u2019s membership invites the popular misconception that this institution is a little different from the two political branches of government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.481,
                                "stop": 288.536,
                                "byte_start": 1186795,
                                "byte_stop": 1230994,
                                "text": "No misconception could do more lasting injury to this Court and to the system of law which it is our abiding mission to serve."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.536,
                                "stop": 305.553,
                                "byte_start": 1230994,
                                "byte_stop": 1299017,
                                "text": "I am authorized to say that Mr. Justice Douglas and Mr. Justice Marshal have joined this dissenting opinion and that Mr. Justice Brennan also agrees that Fuentes versus Shevin requires reversal of the judgment of the Supreme Court of Louisiana."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
